}

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width,initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>SkillSwap Cookie Policy</title>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;600&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: 'Inter',sans-serif;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            background: #fff;
            color: #333;
        }

        header {
            background: #16a085;
            color: #fff;
            padding: 20px;
            text-align: center;
        }

        nav {
            background: #f9f9f0;
            border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd;
        }

            nav ul {
                display: flex;
                flex-wrap: wrap;
                justify-content: center;
                margin: 0;
                padding: 0;
                list-style: none;
            }

            nav a {
                padding: 12px 18px;
                text-decoration: none;
                color: #555;
                font-weight: 600;
            }

                nav a.active, nav a:hover {
                    color: #16a085;
                }

        .container {
            max-width: 900px;
            margin: 30px auto;
            padding: 0 20px;
        }

        h1 {
            margin: 0;
            font-size: 2rem;
            color: #16a085;
        }

        h2 {
            margin-top: 2.5rem;
            font-size: 1.5rem;
            color: #16a085;
        }

        p, ul {
            margin: 1rem 0;
            line-height: 1.6;
        }

        .short-version {
            background: #f0f4f8;
            padding: 15px;
            border-radius: 5px;
        }

            .short-version h2 {
                margin-top: 0;
            }

        footer {
            text-align: center;
            margin: 50px 0;
            font-size: 0.9rem;
            color: #777;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <header>
        <h1>Cookie Policy</h1>
        <p>Last updated: May 14, 2025</p>
    </header>

    <nav>
        <ul>
            <li><a href="#short" class="active">Short Version</a></li>
            <li><a href="#1">1. What Are Cookies?</a></li>
            <li><a href="#2">2. Types of Cookies</a></li>
            <li><a href="#3">3. Third-Party Cookies</a></li>
            <li><a href="#4">4. Managing Cookies</a></li>
            <li><a href="#5">5. Contact</a></li>
        </ul>
    </nav>

    <div class="container">

        <!-- Short Version -->
        <section id="short" class="short-version">
            <h2>The Short Version</h2>
            <p><strong>Cookies:</strong> Small text files placed on your device to store preferences, track usage, and enable core functionality.</p>
            <p><strong>Why We Use Them:</strong> Essential site operation, performance analytics, and, with consent, marketing.</p>
            <p><strong>Your Control:</strong> You can block or delete cookies via your browser settings—but essential features may break.</p>
        </section>

        <!-- 1. What Are Cookies? -->
        <section id="1">
            <h2>1. What Are Cookies?</h2>
            <p>Cookies are small data files stored on your device when you visit a website. They help remember your settings (language, login status), understand how you use the site, and provide a smoother experience.</p>
        </section>

        <!-- 2. Types of Cookies -->
        <section id="2">
            <h2>2. Types of Cookies We Use</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Essential Cookies:</strong> Required for login, session management, and security.</li>
                <li><strong>Performance Cookies:</strong> Collect anonymous statistics on site usage (via Google Analytics).</li>
                <li><strong>Functional Cookies:</strong> Remember your preferences (language, display).</li>
                <li><strong>Marketing Cookies:</strong> Track browsing to show relevant ads (third-party).</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- 3. Third-Party Cookies -->
        <section id="3">
            <h2>3. Third-Party Cookies</h2>
            <p>We integrate features from partners (e.g., Stripe, Facebook). These third parties may set their own cookies; their use is governed by their own policies.</p>
        </section>

        <!-- 4. Managing Cookies -->
        <section id="4">
            <h2>4. Managing Cookies</h2>
            <p>You can control or delete cookies through your browser settings:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Chrome: Settings → Privacy → Cookies and other site data</li>
                <li>Firefox: Options → Privacy & Security → Cookies</li>
                <li>Edge: Settings → Privacy & Services → Cookies</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Disabling essential cookies may prevent the site from functioning properly.</p>
        </section>

        <!-- 5. Contact -->
        <section id="5">
            <h2>5. Contact Us</h2>
            <p>Questions about this policy? Email  <a href="mailto:skillswap360@gmail.com">skillswap360@gmail.com</a>.</p>
        </section>

        <footer>&copy; 2025 SkillSwap. All rights reserved.</footer>
    </div>

    <script>
        document.querySelectorAll('nav a').forEach(link => {
          link.addEventListener('click', e => {
            document.querySelectorAll('nav a').forEach(l => l.classList.remove('active'));
            e.target.classList.add('active');
          });
        });
    </script>
</body>
</html>
